# Developer / soak diagnostics only — NOT player settings.
#
# File format (parser: port/debug_env.c):
#   - UTF-8 text, one assignment per line: NAME=value
#   - Optional leading "export " stripped
#   - Optional single- or double-quotes around value
#   - Lines starting with # are comments; blank lines ignored
#   - Allowed names: SSB64_* , CURL_CA_BUNDLE , SSL_CERT_FILE (all others skipped)
#   - Applied only when not already set in the process environment
#
# Desktop: copy to your BattleShip user-data folder as debug.env (same dir as ssb64.log).
#   macOS: ~/Library/Application Support/BattleShip/debug.env
#
# Android: Settings → Tools → "Restart with debug.env" — pick ANY file with this
#   content; it is stored as .../Android/data/<package>/files/debug.env .
#   Or: adb push scripts/debug.env.example /sdcard/Android/data/<package>/files/debug.env
#   then use "Restart with debug.env" once (normal launch does not load debug.env).
#
# Full SSB64_* list: docs/netplay_environment_variables.md

SSB64_NETPLAY_DELAY_SYNC_DIAG=1
# SSB64_NETPLAY_FRAME_COMMIT_DIAG=2
# SSB64_MATCHMAKING_BASE_URL=https://your-dev-server.example
